---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Mac & Apple Software | Jake Fixes Tech — Littleton, NH"
description="macOS reinstalls, software troubleshooting, iCloud help and Linux installs on older Macs. Serving Littleton NH and the North Country. Software only, no Apple hardware repairs.">

  <!-- Header Banner -->
  <section style="position:relative;overflow:hidden;background-color:rgb(30,64,175);">
    <img src="/hero.jpg" alt="Professional tech workspace with dual monitors" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" style="position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;z-index:0;" />
    <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(30,64,175,0.88),rgba(37,99,235,0.88));z-index:1;"></div>
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;padding:4rem 1.5rem;text-align:center;position:relative;z-index:2;">
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#93c5fd;">
        <a href="/services" style="color:#93c5fd;text-decoration:none;" aria-label="Back to all services">← Services</a>
      </p>
      <h1 style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;color:white;line-height:1.2;">Mac & Apple Software</h1>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;color:#bfdbfe;line-height:1.75;font-size:1.1rem;max-width:42rem;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
        macOS reinstalls, software troubleshooting, iCloud help, and Linux installs on older Macs. Software support only — no Apple hardware repairs.
      </p>
      <div style="margin-top:1.5rem;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;">
        <a href="/contact" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:white;color:#1e40af;font-weight:700;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;">
          Book a Repair
          <svg style="height:1rem;width:1rem;" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/pricing" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);color:white;font-weight:600;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);">
          View Pricing
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Info Bar -->
  <section style="background:#1e40af;padding:1.25rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:2rem;text-align:center;">
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">Software Only</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">No Apple Hardware Repairs</div>
      </div>
      <div style="width:1px;height:2.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);flex-shrink:0;"></div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">macOS + Linux</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">All Software Options Covered</div>
      </div>
      <div style="width:1px;height:2.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);flex-shrink:0;"></div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">2012 – 2018</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">Mac Models for Linux Installs</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I Do -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">Mac Services</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">What I Can Help With</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">From a sluggish Mac that needs a fresh OS install to an older machine that Apple stopped supporting, there are more options than most people realize. Here's what I offer for Mac and Apple software support.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #2563eb;">
          <div class="service-num" style="background:#eff6ff;color:#1e40af;">🍎</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">macOS Reinstall & Upgrade</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">If your Mac is running slow, behaving strangely, or you just want a clean slate, a fresh macOS install can make a big difference. I handle the full process including making sure you're on the right version for your hardware and that your data is backed up before anything gets touched.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #7c3aed;">
          <div class="service-num" style="background:#f5f3ff;color:#6d28d9;">🔧</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">macOS Software Troubleshooting</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">Apps crashing, slow performance, weird system behavior, startup issues — these are all software problems that can often be fixed without wiping anything. I diagnose what's going on and take the most targeted approach to get your Mac running the way it should.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #0369a1;">
          <div class="service-num" style="background:#e0f2fe;color:#0369a1;">☁️</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">iCloud Troubleshooting</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">iCloud syncing issues, photos not loading, storage problems, sign-in errors — iCloud can be frustrating when it doesn't work right. I can help sort out most iCloud software issues and get things syncing properly again.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #15803d;">
          <div class="service-num" style="background:#f0fdf4;color:#15803d;">💾</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">Time Machine Backup Setup</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">Time Machine is one of the best backup tools available on any platform but a lot of Mac users have never set it up or don't know if it's actually running. I can get it configured properly so your files are automatically backed up without you having to think about it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Linux on Old Macs -->
  <section style="background:white;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">Give It New Life</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">Your Old Mac Isn't Dead. It Just Needs Linux.</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">Apple stops releasing macOS updates for older hardware after a certain point. When that happens, most people think their machine is done. It isn't. Mac hardware from 2012 to 2018 can often run Linux beautifully, and in many cases it'll run faster than it ever did on macOS.</p>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">I install Linux Mint Cinnamon as my go-to distro. It's stable, user-friendly, and looks familiar enough that most people pick it up quickly. But here's where it gets interesting — Linux has an enormous range of design and customization options. If you want it to look and feel exactly like macOS, that's possible. If you want something completely different and visually striking, that's possible too. The possibilities are genuinely limitless in a way that Windows and macOS simply aren't.</p>
      </div>

      <div id="linux-grid">
        <div class="linux-card">
          <span class="linux-icon">🚀</span>
          <h3>Dramatically Faster</h3>
          <p>Linux is lightweight by nature. Older Mac hardware that struggled under macOS often runs noticeably faster with Linux installed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="linux-card">
          <span class="linux-icon">🎨</span>
          <h3>Unlimited Customization</h3>
          <p>Want it to look like macOS with a Plank dock and the WhiteSur theme? Done. Want something totally unique? Also done. Linux lets you design your desktop however you want.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="linux-card">
          <span class="linux-icon">🔒</span>
          <h3>Secure & Supported</h3>
          <p>Linux Mint receives regular security updates. No more running an unsupported OS that Apple has abandoned.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="linux-card">
          <span class="linux-icon">💸</span>
          <h3>Free Forever</h3>
          <p>Linux is completely free. No subscription, no license fee, no upgrade costs. You own it outright just like your hardware.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Honest Limitations -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">Honest Expectations</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">What You Should Know Before You Come In</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">I'd rather be upfront about limitations than have you leave disappointed. Here are the honest things worth knowing about Mac software support.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">

        <div class="limit-item">
          <span style="font-size:1.5rem;flex-shrink:0;">🔑</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Apple Account Lockouts Are Apple's Problem</h3>
            <p>If you've forgotten your Apple ID credentials and your Mac is locked, that recovery process goes through Apple directly. It can be a lengthy process and it's not something I handle. Apple Support is the right call for account-level lockouts.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="limit-item">
          <span style="font-size:1.5rem;flex-shrink:0;">📶</span>
          <div>
            <h3>WiFi May Not Work Out of the Box on Linux</h3>
            <p>Many older Macs use Broadcom WiFi cards that have limited Linux driver support. In some cases WiFi works perfectly, in others it requires extra steps, and in some configurations it may not work at all. Ethernet always works reliably. I'll be upfront about what to expect for your specific model before the install happens.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="limit-item">
          <span style="font-size:1.5rem;flex-shrink:0;">⚠️</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Not Every Mac Is a Good Candidate</h3>
            <p>Some Mac models have hardware quirks, thermal issues, or firmware limitations that can make any software work difficult regardless of what OS you're running. Results vary by model and year. I'll check your specific machine before committing to anything and tell you honestly what's realistic.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="limit-item">
          <span style="font-size:1.5rem;flex-shrink:0;">🔩</span>
          <div>
            <h3>No Apple Hardware Repairs</h3>
            <p>Cracked screens, bad batteries, broken keyboards, logic board issues — I do not work on Apple hardware at all. Software support only. For hardware repairs, Apple or an Apple Authorized Service Provider is the right place.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1e40af,#2563eb);padding:4rem 1.5rem;text-align:center;">
    <div style="max-width:40rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:white;margin-bottom:1rem;">Got a Mac That Needs Help?</h2>
      <p style="color:#bfdbfe;font-size:1.1rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:2rem;">Whether it needs a fresh macOS install, some software troubleshooting, or a new life with Linux, reach out and let's figure out the best path forward for your machine.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;">
        <a href="/contact" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:white;color:#2563eb;font-weight:700;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;">
          <svg style="height:1.25rem;width:1.25rem;" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg>
          Get in Touch
        </a>
        <a href="tel:+18022341552" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);color:white;font-weight:600;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);">
          <svg style="height:1.25rem;width:1.25rem;" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 0 1 4.69 12a19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 3.6 1.28h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72c.127.96.361 1.903.7 2.81a2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L7.91 8.96a16 16 0 0 0 6.29 6.29l.54-.54a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45c.907.339 1.85.573 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 21.28 17z"/></svg>
          (802) 234-1552
        </a>
      </div>
      <p style="color:#bfdbfe;font-size:0.875rem;margin-top:1.5rem;">
        <a href="/services" style="color:#bfdbfe;text-decoration:underline;" aria-label="Back to all services">← Back to All Services</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .service-item {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .service-num {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    height: 3rem;
    width: 3rem;
    min-width: 3rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .item-title {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .item-desc {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  #linux-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .linux-card {
    background: #f8fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .linux-icon {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .linux-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .linux-card p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .limit-item {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .limit-item h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .limit-item p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .service-item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    #linux-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .limit-item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>